children.name: BUILTIN
children.description: Default errors for the ExtendableError type

children.name: RANGE_ERROR
children.description: The RangeError object indicates an error when a value is not in the set or range of allowed values.

children.name: REFERENCE_ERROR
children.description: The ReferenceError object represents an error when a non-existent variable is referenced.

children.name: SYNTAX_ERROR
children.description: The SyntaxError object represents an error when trying to interpret syntactically invalid code.

children.name: TYPE_ERROR
children.description: The TypeError object represents an error when a value is not of the expected type.

children.name: URI_ERROR
children.description: The URIError object represents an error when a global URI handling function was used in a wrong way.
